text: Massy (former name: Lenin-Jol) is a large village in Jalal-Abad Region, Kyrgyzstan. Its population was 13,880 in 2009. It is the center of the Massy aiyl okmotu (rural community) and Nooken District. The Bishkek - Osh highway passing through Massy goes west to Kochkor-Ata and east to Bazar-Korgon and Jalal-Abad city. ==References== Category:Populated places in Jalal-Abad Region
title: Massy, Kyrgyzstan
